<subSubSection id="C3236569FFF06A13136CFF0BFE4ED28F" pageId="49" pageNumber="158" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8636E2FFF06A13136CFF0BFEAFD092" blockId="49.[111,649,216,749]" box="[113,258,216,242]" pageId="49" pageNumber="158">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8636E2FFF06A13136CFF2BFE4ED28F" blockId="49.[111,649,216,749]" pageId="49" pageNumber="158">
Shells small,L to 5.0 mm, H to 
<quantity id="4CC19B07FFF06A1312B9FF2BFE58D170" box="[420,501,248,274]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="49" pageNumber="158" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5mm</quantity>
, white or pink, solid, subcircular, anteriorly extended (H/L 0.97), inflated (T/L 0.4). Posterior sulcus prominent.Lunule small, heart-shaped.Sculpture of prominent, fl aring, regularly spaced, undulate commarginal lamellae. Interspaces with low radial ribs. Shell surface with linear punctations (
<figureCitation id="13022A67FFF06A131229FE65FE20D1B2" box="[308,397,438,464]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="50.[113,124,1634,1651]" captionTargetBox="[196,1154,215,1528]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIG. 31. — Cardiolucina undula n. sp., LAGON, stn DW 149, New Caledonia: A, exterior of right valve; B, dorsal view; C, D, interior of left and right valves; E, exterior of right valve; F, detail of shell surface; A, B, F, holotype (MNHN); C-E, paratype (MNHN). Scale bars: A-E, 1.0 mm; F, 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5392355" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5392355/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="158">Fig. 31F</figureCitation>
). Radial sculpture absent in anterior and posterior dorsal areas. Commarginal lamellae more closely spaced on juvenile shells. Hinge teeth: LV with 2 small cardinal teeth and large anterior and posterior laterals, RV with 2 cardinal teeth, the anterior much smaller, and anterior and posterior lateral sockets. Anterior adductor muscle scar short, detached for 1/5 of length. Pallial line continuous. Interior shell margin crenulate, finer crenulae anteriorly and posteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3236569FFF06A13136CFCC0FDD5D428" pageId="49" pageNumber="158" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8636E2FFF06A13136CFCC0FF78D349" blockId="49.[111,648,787,1098]" box="[113,213,787,813]" pageId="49" pageNumber="158">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8636E2FFF06A13136CFCE1FDD5D428" blockId="49.[111,648,787,1098]" pageId="49" pageNumber="158">
Previously, Taylor &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA84B13FFF06A13124FFCE1FD8ED32E" author="GLOVER E. A. &amp; TAYLOR J. D." box="[338,547,818,844]" pageId="49" pageNumber="158" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref35909" refString="GLOVER E. A. &amp; TAYLOR J. D. 1997. - New species and records of Rastafaria and Megaxinus from the western Indian Ocean and Red Sea, with a reappraisal of Megaxinus. Journal of Conchology 36: 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="1997">Glover (1997: 102)</bibRefCitation>
included samples of this species from 
<collectingCountry id="F32E7672FFF06A131287FC81FD90D30E" box="[410,573,850,876]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="49" pageNumber="158">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
within 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D61FFF06A13136CFCA1FE45D3EE" authority="(Yokoyama, 1927)" baseAuthorityName="Yokoyama" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[113,488,882,908]" class="Bivalvia" family="Lucinidae" genus="Cardiolucina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinida" pageId="49" pageNumber="158" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="civica">
<emphasis id="B94DEAF0FFF06A13136CFCA1FE86D3EE" box="[113,299,882,908]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="158">Cardiolucina civica</emphasis>
(Yokoyama,1927)
</taxonomicName>
, but that species is larger, has a more circular shell and more prominent radial ribs.Another similar species is 
<taxonomicName id="4C394D61FFF06A1312CEFC62FF02D389" authority="(Hedley, 1909)" baseAuthorityName="Hedley" baseAuthorityYear="1909" class="Bivalvia" family="Lucinidae" genus="Cardiolucina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinida" pageId="49" pageNumber="158" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rugosa">
<emphasis id="B94DEAF0FFF06A1312CEFC62FD83D3A9" box="[467,558,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="158">C. rugosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA84B13FFF06A131125FC62FF0AD389" author="HEDLEY C." pageId="49" pageNumber="158" pagination="420 - 466" refId="ref36193" refString="HEDLEY C. 1909. - Mollusca from the Hope Islands, North Queensland. Proceedings of the Linnean Society of New South Wales 34: 420 - 466." type="journal article" year="1909">Hedley, 1909</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
of the W Pacific but this is smaller (
<emphasis id="B94DEAF0FFF06A131102FC02FD82D389" box="[543,559,977,1003]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="158">c.</emphasis>
3.0 mm shell length), with relatively larger hinge teeth, the commarginal lamellae less conspicuously folded and the inner shell margin with far fewer crenulations.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
